The Dicks had moved to San Francisco at one point, but when they chose to return to Austin, Gary Floyd stayed behind, forming Sister Double Happiness with former Dicks drummer Lynn Perko in 1986. The new group wallowed in furious, blues-tinged hard rock fueled by Floyd's dynamic belting ability. The band sparked enough interest to sign to major-label Reprise for 1991's Heart & Mind. The group broke up in 1995, however, and Floyd moved on to form the Gary Floyd Band, which released the album Broken Angels in 1995. Floyd released the solo effort, Backdoor Preacher Man, in 2000. He went on to front The Progrock band Laugh In The Dark in the 70’s, and in 1975 founded the celebrated instrumental rock fusion band Woodenhead.
